{{Infobox motorsport venue| Name = Alastaro Circuit | Nicknames = | Time = | Location = [[Loimaa]], [[Finland]]| Coordinates = | Image = [[Image:Alastaron moottorirata.jpg|250px]] | Image_caption = Alastaro track profile.| Capacity = | Owner = | Operator = | Broke_ground = | Opened = | Closed = | Construction_cost= | Architect = | Former_names = | Events = [[SMP F4 Championship]], EC Drag Race, RR Scandinavian Open, NEZ Racing Championship | Layout1 = | Surface = | Length_km = 2.721| Length_mi = 1.691| Turns = 11| Banking = | Record_time = 1:11.437| Record_driver = [[Andrea Belicchi]]| Record_team = [[Lukoil Racing]]| Record_year = 2003| Record_class = [[Finnish Formula Three Championship|F3]]| }}
The '''Alastaro Circuit''' is a racing circuit situated in [[Virttaa]] village in [[Loimaa]], Finland. The track is {{Convert|3.00|km|mi|2}} long. There are also "jokamiesluokka" ([[folkrace]]) and [[drag racing]] tracks in the same area.
The circuit is named after [[List of former municipalities of Finland|former municipality]] of [[Finland]]. It was merged to town of [[Loimaa]] in 2009.
Track info:
* Length: 2721 metres (1.691 miles) * Length of folkrace track: 1,800 metres (1.12 miles) * Run: clockwise * Width: 12–15 metres (39–49&nbsp;ft)
