'''''Tai Chi Single Whip''''' (or '''''Taichi Single Whip''''') is an outdoor sculpture by Taiwanese artist [[Ju Ming]], installed in [[Montreal]]'s [[Victoria Square, Montreal|Victoria Square]], in [[Quebec]], Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/montreal-art-celebrates-carey-price-s-record-breaking-season-1.3028067|title=Even Montreal's public art has Habs fever|website=Cbc.ca|accessdate=10 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vancouverbiennale.com/artists/ju-ming/|title=Ju Ming|date=25 August 2014|website=Vancouverbiennale.com|accessdate=10 August 2017}}</ref>
