{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Weightlifting Federation of Africa |abbrev = WFA |logo = WFA emblem.jpeg |logosize = 150px |sport = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|1978}} |aff = [[International Weightlifting Federation]] |affdate = |region = |regionyear = |regionserved =Africa |headquarters = [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]] |location = |president = Khaled Mhalhel<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.iwf.net/focus-on-iwf/federations/continental-federations/ | title=Continental Federations | publisher=International Weightlifting Federation | accessdate=11 September 2015}}</ref> |chairman = |secretary = Eshelly Manareddin |url = |countryflag = |more = }}
The '''Weightlifting Federation of Africa''' was founded in 1978. The federation is the body that governs and oversees [[Olympic weightlifting|weightlifting]] sports in Africa.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.iwf.net/2012/11/12/coming-up-african-youth-and-junior-championships-in-tunis/ | title=Coming up: African Youth and Junior Championships in Tunis | publisher=International Weightlifting Federation | accessdate=11 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Encyclopedia of Associations: International organizations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jj4aAQAAMAAJ|year=2003|publisher=Gale|isbn=978-0-8103-8957-1|page=1014}}</ref>
